From: rogerj@goya.its.rpi.edu (Diversion (Jeff Rogers))
Subject: Re: Is there any undelete program for Linux?
Date: 25 Sep 1993 22:19:06 GMT

leij@mentor.cc.purdue.edu (Jason Lei) writes:

>I wonder if there is any undelete program like "unrm" for Linux?

Not that I'm aware of, but there are certain things you can do:

1) alias rm to something like mv $* /tmp/unrmable and have a cron job clean
out that dir every day/hour/whatever. Then, just unrm stuff from that
directory. 

2) Search your archives for Linus's story about wiping out his entire kernel
source dir (or something like that) and recovered it by hacking fsck.
Something like taking advantage of the fact that the minix filesystem
doesn't do synchronous updates. 

3) Get an optical WORM drive ;-)

Diversion

