From: joe@apache.dtcc.edu (Joe Brown)
Subject: Re: procps (getit) (was:  Re: Linux patches to top?)
Date: 25 Sep 1993 20:55:36 -0400

In article <282n2s$a7g@usenet.rpi.edu> ryanm4@hall106.its.rpi.edu (Matthew J. Ryan) writes:
>
>extern "C" blah blah
>       ^^^
> The stuff compiled when I removed this, but then the kernel would
>not compile without it.  Anyone know why its giving a parse error?
>

That is an C++ external declaration.  Since the compiler isn't in C++
mode, it doesn't recognize this syntax.

pl13 should clear these troubles up nicely, since C++ code has been
removed from the sources.
