From: haynes@cats.ucsc.edu (James H. Haynes)
Subject: Re: Is there any undelete program for Linux?
Date: 26 Sep 1993 01:59:24 GMT


as someone else mentioned, no but you can alias rm to something else.

There's a pretty elaborate package called 'delete' available from
sipb.mit.edu.  It works by renaming files from mumble to .#mumble;
then there are tools to undelete, and to purge the files marked for
deletion, either all at once or selectively.
-- 
haynes@cats.ucsc.edu
